      • addRelation

        public void addRelation(InputParameter fatherParameter,
                        Object singleValue,
                        InputParameter subParameter)
                 throws InputParameter.NotValidParameterValue
        Adds a relation between two parameters. A relation is some values related with an input parameter who is a subparameter
        Parameters:
        subParameter - The son parameter
        singleValue - The value that creaters the relation between the son and the father parameter
        fatherParameter - The father parameter
        Throws:
        InputParameter.NotValidParameterValue - Throws this when the the value that makes the relation is not a possible value of the father parameter

        Parameters:

        values - A list of values that relates the son parameter with the father parameter
        fatherParameter - The father parameter
        Throws:
